{"contents":[{"parts":[{"text":"Calculate 23 * 17. Show your work."}],"role":"user"},{"parts":[{"text":"To calculate **23 × 17**, you can use several methods. Here are two ways to show the work:\n\n### Method 1: Standard Long Multiplication\n1.  **Multiply 23 by 7 (the ones digit):**\n    *   7 × 3 = 21 (Write down 1, carry the 2)\n    *   7 × 2 = 14\n    *   14 + 2 (carried) = 16\n    *   Result: **161**\n\n2.  **Multiply 23 by 10 (the tens digit):**\n    *   Place a 0 in the ones column.\n    *   1 × 3 = 3\n    *   1 × 2 = 2\n    *   Result: **230**\n\n3.  **Add the two results together:**\n    *   161 + 230 = **391**\n\n**Work Layout:**\n```text\n      23\n    x 17\n    ----\n     161  (7 × 23)\n    +230  (10 × 23)\n    ----\n     391\n```\n\n***\n\n### Method 2: Difference of Squares (Mental Math Trick)\nSince 23 and 17 are both the same distance (3) from 20, you can use the algebraic formula $(a + b)(a - b) = a^2 - b^2$.\n\n1.  Rewrite the numbers: $(20 + 3) \\times (20 - 3)$\n2.  Apply the formula: $20^2 - 3^2$\n3.  Calculate the squares: $400 - 9$\n4.  Final result: **391**\n\n**Final Answer:**\n23 × 17 = **391**","thoughtSignature":""}],"role":"model"},{"parts":[{"text":"Now divide that result by 23"}],"role":"user"}],"generationConfig":{"candidateCount":1,"maxOutputTokens":1024,"temperature":0.5,"topK":3,"topP":0.95},"safetySettings":[{"category":"HARM_CATEGORY_DANGEROUS_CONTENT","threshold":"BLOCK_NONE"},{"category":"HARM_CATEGORY_HARASSMENT","threshold":"BLOCK_NONE"},{"category":"HARM_CATEGORY_HATE_SPEECH","threshold":"BLOCK_NONE"},{"category":"HARM_CATEGORY_SEXUALLY_EXPLICIT","threshold":"BLOCK_NONE"}]}HTTP/2.0 200 OK
