      "content": {
        "parts": [
          {
            "text": "To divide **391** by **23**, you can use the relationship from the previous multiplication or perform long division.\n\n### Method 1: Using the Inverse Relationship\nSince you just calculated that **23 × 17 = 391**, division is the inverse operation:\n$$391 \\div 23 = 17$$\n\n---\n\n### Method 2: Long Division\n1.  **How many times does 23 go into 39?**\n    *   23 goes into 39 **1** time.\n    *   $1 \\times 23 = 23$\n    *   $39 - 23 = 16$\n\n2.  **Bring down the 1:**\n    *   This makes the new number **161**.\n\n3.  **How many times does 23 go into 161?**\n    *   From our previous work, we know $23 \\times 7 = 161$.\n    *   So, 23 goes into 161 exactly **7** times.\n    *   $161 - 161 = 0$\n\n**Work Layout:**\n```text\n      17\n    ____\n 23 ) 391\n    - 23\n    ----\n      161\n    - 161\n    ----\n        0\n```\n\n**Final Answer:**\n391 ÷ 23 = **17**",
            "thoughtSignature": ""
          }
        ],
        "role": "model"
      },
      "finishReason": "STOP",
      "index": 0
